What an amazing day and great turnout for our Hike For Toys event! Together we’ve collected over 100 toys which will brighten this holiday season for foster youth across Los Angeles, Riverside, and San Bernardino County. To everyone who attended and participated, words cannot express how much we appreciate your generosity! ❤️❤️ Special thanks to @always_ca @badasshikingwomen @hikeinlandempire @theoutdoors.life @switchbackchics and @lazyasshiking for making this event a success. You all rock! 🎄🤗

Hi everyone, @noeliaatravels and @matthikes7.0 here! Friendly REMINDER that our next meet-up is taking place next Saturday, December 9th! Join @always_ca @badasshikingwomen @hikeinlandempire @peoplewhoadventure @switchbackchics and @theoutdoors.life for our Holiday Hike for Toys event 🎁🎄. The venue will be the Baldy Notch since there’s a restaurant, and it’s easily accessible with the option to take the Ski Lift up. Everyone is encouraged to bring one unopened toy. You will receive one raffle ticket for every toy you bring. All toys will be donated to a local Foster Family Agency within our community that serves underprivileged youth. We’ll meet at the Ski Lift from 9-10:30am, where we’ll gather toys and hand out raffle tickets. The hike starts at 11am and the raffle will begin at 2:30. Hope to see everyone there! ❄️❤️

Baldy. We'll be starting at 11:00am and head up to the restaurant for drinks, food, and mingling. Some of you are familiar with Baldy and know there's a few options to get to the Notch, most of us will be starting at the Ski Lifts and take the fire road up. Event is scheduled from 11am to 5pm. It’s that time again, our next meet-up is here! Always Ca, Badass Hiking Women, Hike Inland Empire, People Who Adventure, Switchback Chics, and The Outdoors Life are coming together for our Holiday Hike for Toys event. The venue will be the Baldy Notch since there’s a restaurant, and it’s easily accessible with the option to take the Ski Lift up. Everyone is encouraged to bring one unopened toy. You will receive one raffle ticket for every toy you bring. All toys will be donated to a local Foster Family Agency within our community that serves underprivileged youth. We’ll meet at the Ski Lift parking lot on December 9th from 9-10:30am, where we’ll gather toys and hand out raffle tickets. The hike starts at 11am and the raffle will begin at 2:30. Hope to see everyone there! All are welcome.

Hi everyone, @noeliaatravels and @matthikes7.0 here, we spent this past weekend conquering a goal we've had for over two years, summiting Mt. Whitney! It felt so amazing to reach the summit, it inspired us to want to do more for our community. The act of hiking has been our path to healing, growth, self-discovery, resilience, and emotional well-being. We want to encourage and motivate others to get outside and experience the countless benefits we've experienced from spending time in nature and pursuing new adventures. We're excited to announce that we have some group hikes in the works and giveaways coming up. Looking forward to connecting with you all. Keep sharing your adventures and stories with us by tagging or using our hashtag
